"title": "6671: grace, and Christian life",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6671: grace, and christian life",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Christian life, from its beginning to its end, is totally dependent upon the grace of God.</p>\n<h2>God's grace compensates for human weaknesses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:8-2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:8–12:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:10\">1PE 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:1-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:1–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:8\">2CO 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:2\">HEB 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:17-2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are to pray for grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:16\">PSA 25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:1-Hos14:2\">HOS 14:1–14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:9\">COL 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:12\">COL 4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Christian experience may be summed up in terms of grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:10\">1CO 15:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:27\">ACT 18:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:2\">ROM 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15\">GAL 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:7\">PHP 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Believers should go on to experience more of God's grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:32\">ACT 20:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:43\">ACT 13:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:3-Col1:6\">COL 1:3–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:9\">HEB 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:12\">1PE 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are enabled to serve Jesus Christ by his grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:39-Acts15:40\">ACT 15:39–15:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:17\">ROM 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6\">ROM 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:15\">ROM 15:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10\">1CO 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7-Eph3:9\">EPH 3:7–3:9</a></p>\n<h2>God's grace is seen in Christian character, especially in generosity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:6-2Cor8:7\">2CO 8:6–8:7</a></strong> <em>Referring to a collection being taken up for the poor Christians in Jerusalem.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:33\">ACT 4:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:22-Acts11:23\">ACT 11:22–11:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:13-2Cor9:14\">2CO 9:13–9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:6\">COL 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>An ongoing experience of God's grace requires the believer's co-operation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1\">2CO 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12-Phil2:13\">PHP 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:15\">HEB 12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a></p>",
